\"><source media=\"(min-width: 768.1px) and (max-width: 834px)\" srcset=\"https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/00wc_notatwork_630.png?width=503&amp;quality=60&amp;crop=3:2&amp;auto=webp 1x, https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/00wc_notatwork_630.png?width=1006&amp;quality=60&amp;crop=3:2&amp;auto=webp 1.1x\"><img class=\"d8f60293\" alt=\"What Not to Do on Your Work Computer\"></picture></span></span></a><div class=\"b65a2bb1\"><a href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/blog/what-not-to-do-on-your-work-computer/\" class=\"db8b8ec9\" data-gtm-trigger=\"click_tracking\" data-event-trigger=\"click\" data-event-data-type=\"click\" data-event-data-trigger=\"module\" data-module-name=\"search_click\" data-module-context=\"inline\" data-module-post_id=\"122779\" data-module-url=\"https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/blog/what-not-to-do-on-your-work-computer/\" data-module-index=\"1\">What Not to Do on Your Work Computer</a><div class=\"b2f5fde6\" data-testid=\"date-updated\">Published December 3, 2019</div><div class=\"d3f39c8a\" data-testid=\"article-summary\"><p>It’s best to assume your work computer is monitored and act accordingly. Here are some less obvious tasks you should be mindful of.</p></div></div></div><div class=\"fd1e4488\" data-testid=\"article\"><a href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/blog/video-call-lighting-tips/\" class=\"d5f80623\" data-gtm-trigger=\"click_tracking\" data-event-trigger=\"click\" data-event-data-type=\"click\" data-event-data-trigger=\"module\" data-module-name=\"search_click\" data-module-context=\"inline\" data-module-post_id=\"149697\" data-module-url=\"https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/blog/video-call-lighting-tips/\" data-module-index=\"2\"><span class=\"a247856e\" data-testid=\"container\"><span class=\"a3ad4c3f\" data-testid=\"placeholder\" style=\"padding-bottom:66.67%\"><span class=\"d9349435\" data-testid=\"lofi\" style=\"background-image:url(https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/